Package: causaldosemc
Title: Matrix Completion for Continuous Treatment Panels
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person(given = "Research",
           family = "Team",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "research@example.org")
Description: Research-use tools for estimating baseline counterfactual outcomes
    in balanced panel data with reversible continuous treatment and zero as the
    control state. The package combines zero-dose masking, washout handling,
    low-rank matrix completion, optional observation weighting, diagnostics,
    bootstrap inference, a cross-fitted doubly robust-style linear effect
    layer with internal Gaussian or kernel GPS weighting, optional CBPS-based
    balancing weights, flexible linear, spline, GAM, tree, or forest-based
    assignment mean models, a SCIA-oriented assignment diagnostic, and linear
    or spline-based second-stage dose-response modeling.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
